===Etymology===
From the Japanese word [[アニメ]] (anime), which in turn is a shortform derived from English [[animation]].

===Noun===
'''anime'''

#Animated television programs that originated in [[Japan]].  Sometimes has a related [[manga]] or [[video game]].  Voice actors for characters in an anime are called [[seiyuu]] for the non-dubbed versions.
#Refers to a style of animation used in anime (1) that has also been adopted by some artists in America and other countries.

